  "text": "Hence, as ρ → ∞ the second term in [CITATION_1] vanishes and the SE approximation using [CITATION_2] converges to the equivalent approximation using [CITATION_3] . Conversely, at low SNR both [CITATION_4] and (27) are O(ρ) so the error in using (27) is also O(ρ). Hence, (27) is a convenient indicator of performance across all SNRs. Equation (27) is a remarkably simple result relating performance to the key parameters ρ, M , L, β (l) and κ. Note that [CITATION_5] requires (L − 1)κ < 1 which supports the above discussion where accurate approximations require L and κ to be small. Also, in the high SNR region, ZF and MMSE become very similar so that [CITATION_6] can also be used as an approximation to E[SNR ZF l ].",
